        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends request to PLM through either SMC or IPI mailbox based on the execution environment. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>For EL1 non-secure AArch64 applications, SMC is used. For other environments, IPI mailbox is used.</para><para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the client instance (used for mailbox, can be NULL for SMC) </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PayloadBuf</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to payload buffer containing command and arguments </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PayloadLen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Length of payload buffer (number of u32 elements) </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ResponseBuf</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to store response values (can be NULL if response not needed) </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ResponseLen</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Length of response buffer (number of u32 elements)</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS on success.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE on failure.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_INVALID_PARAM If input parameters are invalid</para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>This is a generic API that internally handles SMC or Mailbox communication based on the build configuration. </para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
<para>Validate input parameters</para><para>Validate mailbox pointer for IPI communication</para><para>Send IPI request to PLM and wait for response</para><para>Cap ResponseLen: the mailbox shift below consumes Response[0], leaving RESPONSE_ARG_CNT - 1 data slots reachable via Response[Idx + 1U].</para><para>Copy IPI response data from InstancePtr-&gt;Response[] into caller&apos;s ResponseBuf. Skip Response[0] (PLM exec status, returned via Status) so ResponseBuf[0] holds the first data word, matching the SMC path layout.</para>        </inbodydescription>
